Give me step by step method using netlify. I have just created a login and made an account. Tell me next

Gemini said
Since you have the account ready, let's get that JSX file live. Because browsers can't read JSX, we have to "build" the project first.

Here are the two ways to do it. Option A is the fastest if you just want a link right now. Option B is better if you plan on making changes later.

Option A: The "Drag & Drop" Method (Fastest)
Use this if you have the project folder on your computer and just want a quick UAT link without dealing with GitHub.

Build your project locally:
Open your terminal in your project folder and run:

Bash
npm run build
This creates a new folder in your project called dist (if using Vite) or build (if using Create React App).

Locate the folder:
Open your file explorer (Finder or Windows Explorer) and find that dist or build folder.

Upload to Netlify:

Log in to your Netlify Dashboard.

Go to the "Sites" tab.

Scroll to the very bottom until you see a gray box that says "Want to deploy a new site without connecting to Git? Drag and drop your site folder here."

Drag the dist or build folder (not the whole project!) into that box.

Get your link:
Netlify will upload the files instantly. Once the "Deploying" status changes to "Published," your UAT link will appear at the top (e.g., fancy-gelato-12345.netlify.app).

Option B: The "Git Sync" Method (Best for UAT)
Use this if you want the UAT link to update automatically every time you fix a bug or change a button.

Push your code to GitHub:
Make sure your project (including the JSX files and package.json) is in a GitHub repository.

Import to Netlify:

On your Netlify dashboard, click the "Add new site" button.

Select "Import from an existing project."

Choose GitHub and authorize Netlify to see your repos.

Configure Settings:

Select your repository.

Netlify usually auto-detects React. Ensure the "Build command" is npm run build and the "Publish directory" is dist or build.

Deploy:

Click "Deploy [Site Name]."

Every time you git push new changes to GitHub, Netlify will automatically update your UAT link.

Important: Fix for "404 on Refresh"
If your UAT link works, but gives you a 404 error when you refresh the page or go to a sub-page (like /login), you need one tiny fix:

Inside your project's public folder, create a new file named _redirects (no file extension).

Paste this single line inside it:

Plaintext
/* /index.html   200
Re-deploy (re-build and drag/drop, or push to GitHub).

